"{\"uid\": \"komonews.com-news-local-coast-guard-aircrew-rescues-hiker-after-adrift-logs-injure-him-hoh-river-olympic-national-park-high-tide-rising-44-help-port-angeles-united-states-uscg\", \"text\": \"Now  43\\u00b0  Fri  54\\u00b0  Sat  52\\u00b0  byAlton Worley II, KOMO News  PORT ANGELES, Wash. -A hiker was rescued by a United States Coast Guard (USCG) aircrew after adrift logs injured him late Saturday night.  The rising tide caused logs to float adrift and injure the 44-year-old man near themouth of the Hoh River. USCG said two others in his party assisted the man before the aircrew from Port Angeles.    The aircrew brought the man to the air station where he received further aid before being taken to Olympic Medical Center.  USCG said the man's current condition is unknown.  2025Sinclair, Inc.\"}"